  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Office Administrator",
  "description": "<h3>Job Summary</h3><p>The Construction Office Administrator provides administrative and clerical support to ensure smooth daily operations of a construction office. This role coordinates documentation, communication, and office processes while supporting project managers, supervisors, and field staff.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Manage daily office operations and administrative tasks</p></li><li><p>Prepare, organize, and maintain construction documents (contracts, permits, submittals, RFIs, change orders)</p></li><li><p>Answer phones, route calls, and handle correspondence (email, mail, courier)</p></li><li><p>Schedule meetings, site visits, and inspections</p></li><li><p>Track project files, drawings, and records (digital and physical)</p></li><li><p>Assist with payroll, timecards, and expense reports</p></li><li><p>Process invoices, purchase orders, and vendor payments</p></li><li><p>Maintain vendor, subcontractor, and client contact information</p></li><li><p>Support project managers with reports, data entry, and document control</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with company procedures and record-keeping standards</p></li><li><p>Order office supplies and coordinate equipment or service needs</p></li></ul><h3>Required Qualifications</h3><ul><li><p>High school diploma or equivalent (associate degree preferred)</p></li><li><p>1–3 years of administrative experience (construction or related industry preferred)</p></li><li><p>Strong organizational and multitasking skills</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook)</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage deadlines in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Strong written and verbal communication skills</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred Skills & Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Familiarity with construction terminology and processes</p></li><li><p>Experience with construction management or accounting software (e.g., Procore, Buildertrend, Sage, QuickBooks)</p></li><li><p>Basic knowledge of invoicing, or bookkeeping</p></li><li><p>Attention to detail and problem-solving skills</p></li></ul><h3>Work Environment</h3><ul><li><p>Office-based with occasional interaction with job sites</p></li><li><p>Full-time (may require occasional overtime depending on project needs)</p></li></ul><h3>Compensation & Benefits</h3><ul><li><p>Competitive pay based on experience</p></li><li><p>Benefits may include health insurance, paid time off, and retirement plans</p></li></ul>",
